soldier settlement
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a policy to assist returned soldiers on to land of their own following the Land Wars, and First and Second World Wars.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: aka soldiers settlement, soldiers' settlement
Citations
Date: 25/9/1902
Source: Hawera & Normanby Star
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: DEPUTATION TO THE PREMIER SUGGESTED SPECIAL SOLDIERS' SETTLEMENT .. A deputation of returned officers and troopers waited on the Minister for Lands yesterday to see if the Government would be prepared to offer them special terms for settling on land in this colony, instead of going to South Africa. The Minister promised to see what could be done, and pointed out that under existing conditions they could form a special settlement.
